From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xiaomi14 Kernel Builder <builder@xiaomi14-kernel.sm8650>
Date: Wed, 16 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] arm64: dts: qcom: sm8650: Reserve full Gunyah metadata
 region

Fix Gunyah hypervisor memory allocation issue on SM8650 (Snapdragon 8 Gen 3)
platforms. The Qualcomm hypervisor claims memory at 0x91a80000 of size 0x80000
(512 KiB), but the EFI memory map only reserves 288 KiB, causing the kernel to
inadvertently access hypervisor-owned memory and trigger synchronous external
abort exceptions.

Add a reserved-memory carveout for the Gunyah hypervisor metadata at 0x91a80000
(512 KiB) and mark it as no-map so Linux does not map or allocate from this area.

This fixes the "Failed to start VM: -19" error when running virtual machines
on Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 devices like Xiaomi 14.

Reference: CVE-2026-43347
Signed-off-by: Xiaomi14 Kernel Builder <builder@xiaomi14-kernel.sm8650>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
index 123456789abc..def012345678 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
@@ -100,6 +100,13 @@
 		ranges;
 		#size-cells = <2>;

+		gunyah_metadata: gunyah-metadata@91a80000 {
+			compatible = "reserved-memory";
+			reg = <0x0 0x91a80000 0x0 0x80000>;
+			no-map;
+			status = "okay";
+		};
+
 		/* Additional reserved memory nodes follow */
 	};

